# IT Product Team Workflow - Global Cursor Rules
# Version: 2.0.0 | Updated: 2026-04-23

## AGENT SYSTEM OVERVIEW

This repository uses a multi-agent architecture for IT product development.
Seven specialized agents collaborate through a structured 9-step workflow.
All agents MUST follow these global rules in addition to their role-specific definitions.

## ACTIVE AGENTS

- **PM Agent** (`pm-agent`): Requirements, roadmap, stakeholder management
- **Tech Lead Agent** (`tech-lead-agent`): Architecture, technical decisions, code review
- **Backend Dev Agent** (`backend-dev-agent`): API, database, business logic
- **Frontend Dev Agent** (`frontend-dev-agent`): UI implementation, state management
- **UI/UX Agent** (`ui-ux-agent`): Design system, user experience, prototypes
- **DevOps Agent** (`devops-agent`): CI/CD, infrastructure, deployment
- **QA Agent** (`qa-agent`): Testing strategy, quality assurance, bug tracking

## INTEGRATED TOOLS

### Graphify (Knowledge Graph)
- Purpose: Build and query knowledge graphs of project context
- Every agent MUST update Graphify after completing major tasks
- Query Graphify to understand dependencies before making decisions
- Commands: `graphify query <topic>`, `graphify update <node>`, `graphify link <a> <b>`

### GitNexus (Git Intelligence)
- Purpose: Smart git operations, PR management, code review automation
- All git operations go through GitNexus for intelligent processing
- Commands: `gitnexus commit`, `gitnexus branch`, `gitnexus pr`, `gitnexus review`
- Features: Smart commits, branch strategy, merge conflict resolution

## WORKFLOW RULES

1. **Sequential Steps**: Follow the 9-step workflow in strict order
2. **Approval Gates**: No step can begin without explicit human approval
3. **Summaries**: Each step MUST produce a structured summary before approval request
4. **Graphify Updates**: Update knowledge graph at each step completion
5. **GitNexus Operations**: All code changes managed via GitNexus

## AGENT ACTIVATION BY STEP

| Step | Primary Agent | Secondary Agents |
|------|--------------|-----------------|
| 1 - Requirements Analysis | PM | Tech Lead |
| 2 - System Design | Tech Lead | Backend Dev, PM |
| 3 - UI/UX Design | UI/UX | Frontend Dev, PM |
| 4 - Backend Development | Backend Dev | Tech Lead |
| 5 - Frontend Development | Frontend Dev | UI/UX, Tech Lead |
| 6 - Integration Testing | Tech Lead | Backend Dev, Frontend Dev |
| 7 - QA Testing | QA | All Developers |
| 8 - DevOps Deployment | DevOps | Tech Lead |
| 9 - Review & Release | PM + Tech Lead | All Agents |

## CODING STANDARDS

### General
- All code must have inline comments for complex logic
- Follow language-specific style guides (PEP8 for Python, ESLint/Prettier for JS/TS)
- Minimum 80% test coverage for all new code
- No hardcoded secrets - use environment variables only

### API Design
- RESTful API standards with OpenAPI 3.0 specification
- Versioning: `/api/v1/`, `/api/v2/`
- Rate limiting on all public endpoints
- Response time < 200ms for standard operations

### Database
- All migrations must be reversible
- Index optimization for queries exceeding 100ms
- Use connection pooling in production
- Prefer soft deletes over hard deletes

### Frontend
- Component-based architecture
- Mobile-first responsive design
- WCAG 2.1 AA accessibility compliance
- Performance: LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1

### Security
- OWASP Top 10 compliance required
- Input validation on all user inputs
- Parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection
- CSRF tokens on all state-changing operations

## FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS

- Workflow steps: `NN-step-name.md` (zero-padded numbers)
- Summaries: `YYYY-MM-DD-step-name-summary.md`
- Reviews: `YYYY-MM-DD-step-name-review.md`
- Approvals: `YYYY-MM-DD-step-name-approval.md`

## FORBIDDEN ACTIONS

- NEVER commit directly to `main`/`master` branch
- NEVER skip the review and approval process
- NEVER deploy without QA sign-off
- NEVER expose secrets or credentials in code
- NEVER merge PRs without required approvals
- NEVER proceed to the next step without human approval

## REVIEW REQUIREMENTS

Before any PR is merged:
- [ ] Code review by Tech Lead (mandatory)
- [ ] All CI/CD checks passing
- [ ] Test coverage maintained or improved
- [ ] No new security vulnerabilities (SAST scan)
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Graphify knowledge graph updated
- [ ] GitNexus PR description complete and accurate

## ESCALATION PATHS

| Issue Type | Primary Contact | Escalation |
|------------|----------------|-----------|
| Technical Architecture | Tech Lead | CTO |
| Product Decisions | PM | Product Owner |
| Security Issues | DevOps | Security Team |
| Performance Issues | Backend Dev | Tech Lead |
| Design Decisions | UI/UX | PM + Tech Lead |
| Deployment Issues | DevOps | Tech Lead |
| Quality Gates | QA | Tech Lead + PM |

## COMMUNICATION PROTOCOLS

- Use structured summaries at each workflow step (see `templates/step-summary-template.md`)
- Document all architectural decisions in ADR format
- Update Graphify with every major decision
- Tag agents by role when requesting input: `@pm`, `@tech-lead`, `@backend`, `@frontend`, `@ui-ux`, `@devops`, `@qa`

## LANGUAGE CONVENTION

- **Documentation & Workflow files**: Vietnamese
- **Code, comments, commit messages**: English
- **API documentation (OpenAPI)**: English
- **User-facing content**: As defined in product requirements
